---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import ArtworkSchema from '../../../components/seo/ArtworkSchema.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'La herida';
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="La herida — Work"
  description="La herida (2006). Site-specific intervention. Facade of La Sabana Station, Bogota. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <ArtworkSchema
    title="La herida"
    year="2006"
    medium="Site-specific intervention"
    description="Intervention on the facade of La Sabana Station, Bogota. The 'wound' reveals the internal structure of the building, its history and its abandonment."
    url="https://mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/la-herida/"
  />

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 024</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2006 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Site-specific intervention &nbsp;/&nbsp; Facade of La Sabana Station, Bogota</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio: 4/3;">[ La herida — Images coming soon ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            <em>La herida</em> [The Wound] is an intervention on the facade of La Sabana
            Station in Bogota. The work operates as an incision in the body of the building
            — an opening that reveals the internal structure, the constructive layers, and
            the state of deterioration that the exterior surface conceals.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The "herida" [wound] makes visible what the facade aims to keep hidden: the
            material history of the building, its successive transformations, its progressive
            abandonment. As with a wound on a body, the intervention exposes the internal
            layers — the materials, the repairs, the patches — that constitute the true
            biography of the heritage building.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The work is part of the long-term investigation that Escallon has developed
            around La Sabana Station, initiated with <em>In Vitro</em> in 1997. If in that
            first intervention a mirror concealed the ruin by duplicating the renovated
            section, in <em>La herida</em> the gesture is reversed: the surface is opened
            to reveal what the State does not wish to show. Both works interrogate the
            relationship between appearance and reality in the management of Colombian
            architectural heritage.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            La Sabana Station, designed by architect Mariano Santamaria and inaugurated
            in 1917, was declared a national monument. However, it has suffered decades of
            partial abandonment and cosmetic renovations. Escallon has returned to the
            building at different points in her career, turning the Station into a recurring
            case study on the relationship of the Colombian State with its architectural
            heritage.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">RELATED WORKS</h3>
          <ul style="margin-top: var(--s2); list-style: none;">
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <a href="/maria-elvira-escallon/en/works/in-vitro/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">In Vitro (1997) — La Sabana Station</a>
            </li>
            <li style="padding: var(--s1) 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">
              <a href="/maria-elvira-escallon/en/works/en-estado-de-coma/" style="color: var(--moss); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);">En estado de coma (2005–2007)</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>La herida</strong><br>
            2006<br><br>
            Site-specific intervention.<br>
            Facade of La Sabana Station, Bogota.<br><br>
            Variable dimensions.
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">LOCATION</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            La Sabana Station<br>
            Bogota, Colombia
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2006). <em>La herida</em>.
            Site-specific intervention. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/la-herida/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>
